1
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:12,767
<i> Looks like Zayn will introduce
Mookie to his</i> mom.

2
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:13,900
<i> Move!</i>

3
00:00:14,033 --> 00:00:15,900
<i>You can never take my daughter
away from me!</i>

4
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:18,067
<i> Aunt Jade!</i>

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,667
<i> I'm so, so sorry.</i>

6
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:25,300
<i>I tried so hard to get
Zayn's mom to like me.</i>

7
00:00:25,433 --> 00:00:27,967
<i> But you ruined everything.</i>

8
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:29,700
<i> Your family's full of drama.</i>

9
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,733
<i> I'm trained to sense danger.</i>

10
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:32,900
<i> And you...</i>

11
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:36,067
<i>you are a risk I refuse to take.</i>

12
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:45,067
<i> Kill her.</i>

13
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,733
<i> Kill her!</i>

14
00:00:46,867 --> 00:00:48,800
<i> You bet I will.</i>

15
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:55,733
<i>I'll make sure that this will be
your last day, Emma.</i>

16
00:00:55,867 --> 00:00:57,067
<i> Goodbye!</i>

17
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:36,767
<i> Mookie, my dear.</i>

18
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,367
<i> I'm now ready to face you.</i>

19
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:39,867
<i> Even if you get mad...</i>

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,100
<i> even if you push me away...</i>

21
00:01:42,267 --> 00:01:44,067
<i> I will tell you everything.</i>

22
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:48,833
I don't want to keep hoping.

23
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:51,067
I'm done with it.

24
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,367
She will never come back.

25
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,567
Ouch!

26
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:07,533
What's wrong with you?
You're so dumb.

27
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:08,567
You don't look where you're
going!

28
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,867
- Move!
- The nerve of you to get mad!

29
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:11,867
Whatever.

30
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,467
Go get the car!

31
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:15,967
Hurry before Emma gets in
trouble!

32
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:18,267
Hurry!

33
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,000
Show me what you got!

34
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:21,667
Darn you!

35
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:27,267
The nerve of you to try
to slap me!

36
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,867
Ouch!

37
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,633
- What's your problem?
- Let me go!

38
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:33,567
Darn you!

39
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:35,667
Show me what you got!

40
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:44,967
- Stop!
- Guard!

41
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:47,933
Emma! Let's go!

42
00:02:48,100 --> 00:02:50,367
Guard!

43
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:53,233
- Let me go! Darn you!
- Come on! Get in the car!

44
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:59,767
Emma!

45
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,100
Emma!

46
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:02,500
Where are you?

47
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:03,867
Emma!

48
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,133
<i> She's gone!</i>

49
00:03:05,267 --> 00:03:06,867
<i> She escaped from you again!</i>

50
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,267
No!

51
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:12,100
I'm not done with you yet, Emma!

52
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:23,233
I didn't mean to do it.

53
00:03:25,667 --> 00:03:30,633
Some kind of demon
is controlling me.

54
00:03:36,567 --> 00:03:43,133
He doesn't leave me alone.
He doesn't stop.

55
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:53,533
But believe me.

56
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:59,000
But believe me.

57
00:03:59,133 --> 00:04:01,467
I want to change so badly.

58
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:06,600
I want to get better.

59
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:09,867
But I don't know how.

60
00:04:12,967 --> 00:04:14,100
Get better?

61
00:04:16,933 --> 00:04:22,867
I consulted a doctor.

62
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:27,600
I was told I have
a mental condition.

63
00:04:32,667 --> 00:04:33,833
Schizo.

64
00:04:36,167 --> 00:04:38,233
Schizoaffective.

65
00:04:38,367 --> 00:04:48,333
A combination of schizo
and bipolar.

66
00:04:50,533 --> 00:04:53,300
I don't remember fully.

67
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:56,733
All I know is I have
a mental condition.

68
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:06,133
When we were still together,

69
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:15,767
there were days when I was
so happy and full of hope.

70
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,133
But...

71
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,500
for an unknown reason,

72
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:28,633
I suddenly felt down.

73
00:05:33,933 --> 00:05:38,300
I was scared and lonely.

74
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:42,333
I kept thinking all sorts
of things.

75
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:51,533
And then they would come.

76
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:54,767
They were whispering.

77
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:57,233
They were whispering
all sorts of things.

78
00:05:59,367 --> 00:06:04,767
"Don't." "Don't."
"Don't trust anyone."

79
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:09,400
"They will only hurt you."

80
00:06:09,567 --> 00:06:11,600
"They will only hurt you."

81
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:16,000
That's why I would get mad.

82
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:19,867
I would explode.

83
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,300
They didn't want to stop.

84
00:06:24,033 --> 00:06:25,800
That's why I would get violent.

85
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:29,533
And you...

86
00:06:32,233 --> 00:06:34,433
I took it out on you.

87
00:06:38,767 --> 00:06:41,267
You were understanding.

88
00:06:41,433 --> 00:06:50,167
But I know you gave up on me
too.

89
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:53,933
I lost you.

90
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:58,700
Because of this darn mind.

91
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:00,167
Because of this darn mind!

92
00:07:00,300 --> 00:07:02,067
Because of this darn mind!

93
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,800
Leave me alone!

94
00:07:03,933 --> 00:07:05,667
Please stop!

95
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:11,067
<i>She must not know that
Jade died,</i>

96
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:21,367
<i>and I, Olive Caparas,
is still so alive.</i>

97
00:07:21,533 --> 00:07:23,300
<i> You're Olive?</i>

98
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:29,400
<i>I'm not crazy, Ligaya! You are!</i>

99
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:37,333
You and Olive have the same
condition.

100
00:07:39,133 --> 00:07:40,867
Sorry, sorry.

101
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,033
Please stop!

102
00:07:43,167 --> 00:07:44,733
Monster!

103
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:46,700
Monster!

104
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,167
Please forgive me, Ligaya!
Please stop!

105
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:48,967
Animal!

106
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:52,233
I'm sorry, Ligaya!

107
00:07:52,367 --> 00:07:53,433
Please stop.

108
00:07:55,633 --> 00:08:03,933
Please stop.

109
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:10,233
The curse of a miserable life
came from you.

110
00:08:13,667 --> 00:08:21,400
I thought it was my fault.
Only to find out it's you.

111
00:08:21,567 --> 00:08:25,533
It came from you.
You're the reason.

112
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:32,133
You're the reason why my
daughter became a monster.

113
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:37,100
And you didn't tell me
that you have a mental problem!

114
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:46,833
It was too late when
I found out.

115
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:50,800
I did everything.

116
00:08:50,933 --> 00:08:52,567
I wanted to do well.

117
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:58,300
So I could give you a good life.

118
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,633
I sold everything.

119
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:09,267
Slippers, umbrella,
fake jewelry,

120
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:12,533
but nothing happened.

121
00:09:12,667 --> 00:09:15,233
I didn't sell much.

122
00:09:15,367 --> 00:09:17,900
I didn't earn enough.

123
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:25,167
That's why I got irritable.

124
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,900
I was irritable.

125
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:34,067
And then you were there
whenever I got home.

126
00:09:35,933 --> 00:09:39,167
A voice was whispering to me.

127
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:43,433
A voice was whispering to me.

128
00:09:43,567 --> 00:09:46,500
It said you were mad at me.

129
00:09:48,467 --> 00:09:50,933
I was worthless.

130
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,467
Useless.

131
00:09:57,567 --> 00:09:59,400
That's why I would hurt you.

132
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:05,700
I almost beat you to death.

133
00:10:09,733 --> 00:10:11,300
I got scared.

134
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:15,967
I consulted a doctor.

135
00:10:17,633 --> 00:10:24,467
When I got home, you were gone.

136
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:30,633
You and our children ran away.

137
00:10:30,767 --> 00:10:32,500
You ran away from me.

138
00:10:42,167 --> 00:10:45,233
I wish I didn't marry you.

139
00:10:45,367 --> 00:10:47,133
I wish I had avoided you.

140
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:50,300
I wish I hadn't had children
with you.

141
00:10:50,433 --> 00:10:52,567
I would've had a happy life.

142
00:10:53,967 --> 00:10:57,333
I wouldn't have suffered.

143
00:10:57,467 --> 00:11:01,600
I wouldn't have questioned
my role as a mother.

144
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:04,933
I wouldn't have questioned
my being.

145
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:06,533
I wish.

146
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:53,967
Here. Look.

147
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:57,433
I wish I hadn't pulled Emma
away. She was gonna help Jade.

148
00:11:57,567 --> 00:12:03,400
We could've seen how
that woman beat her.

149
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:10,000
Look. I will play it again.
She kicked Jade.

150
00:12:10,133 --> 00:12:11,000
Deserve.

151
00:12:12,433 --> 00:12:14,267
Go on. You can scold me.

152
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:19,033
What for?

153
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,267
Emma, you're old enough.

154
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:24,933
You know what you did wrong.

155
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:30,700
I'm just annoyed that you
couldn't control yourself.

156
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:33,967
You lost your focus again.

157
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:39,267
Logan, I didn't lose my focus.

158
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:42,267
I'm determined to show up
to Mookie.

159
00:12:43,367 --> 00:12:46,367
Because I feel like I'm
punishing Mookie

160
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:48,267
whenever I torture Jade.

161
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:51,267
I want to be with Mookie
so badly.

162
00:12:52,433 --> 00:12:55,433
Even if she might not
believe and trust me,

163
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:58,400
I won't stop making her feel
my love.

164
00:13:00,133 --> 00:13:04,500
I will wait for the day
that she can call me Mom again.

165
00:13:07,167 --> 00:13:09,000
Oh, dear.

166
00:13:09,133 --> 00:13:11,333
I can't do anything if
that's what you want.

167
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:15,333
But, Emma, remember this.

168
00:13:15,467 --> 00:13:17,500
No one will replace Jade's
medication anymore.

169
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:21,367
Once she takes the Pryvaxil,

170
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:23,767
she will return to her senses

171
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:28,200
and make sure you can't take
Mookie back.

172
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:31,833
Then, let's fight her head-on.

173
00:13:31,967 --> 00:13:34,267
I will no longer hide
in Jade's insanity.

174
00:13:35,667 --> 00:13:37,667
I will show up to her.

175
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,067
To her and Danilo.

176
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,433
I'm ready, Logan.

177
00:13:42,567 --> 00:13:46,633
I will give her the war
that will take her down

178
00:13:46,767 --> 00:13:48,600
and put her where
she belongs...

179
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,233
in hell.

180
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:14,900
You're lucky I have a
conscience.

181
00:14:15,033 --> 00:14:16,467
I have a heart...

182
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:21,533
unlike you.

183
00:14:31,433 --> 00:14:32,633
Give me the keys.

184
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:36,433
I'm leaving.

185
00:14:37,467 --> 00:14:41,567
But please,
don't look for me anymore.

186
00:14:54,267 --> 00:14:56,000
Give me the keys.

187
00:14:58,667 --> 00:14:59,700
I'm leaving.

188
00:15:00,667 --> 00:15:01,933
But please,

189
00:15:03,033 --> 00:15:04,600
don't look for me anymore.

190
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:11,100
When you expose Olive,

191
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:15,667
will you help your son-in-law
send her to jail?

192
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:28,967
You said you wanted
to help our daughter.

193
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:33,000
You wanted to bring her
to a doctor.

194
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:37,467
Do that, Ligaya.

195
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:40,667
Have Olive treated.

196
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:45,800
She still has hope.

197
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,867
I'm already hopeless.

198
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:03,833
Stay here.

199
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:06,667
Regain your strength.

200
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:11,100
Get ready for your plan.

201
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:14,600
Think about it carefully.

202
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:23,700
Do you think I'll
stay here with you?

203
00:16:34,633 --> 00:16:35,567
No.

204
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:40,033
I'll stay away.

205
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,700
I won't bother you.

206
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:50,200
I'll leave food at the door.

207
00:16:50,333 --> 00:16:52,100
I won't show myself to you.

208
00:16:53,533 --> 00:16:57,067
Tell me once you're ready.

209
00:16:59,067 --> 00:17:04,000
I'll help you see your friends.

210
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:28,667
I'm happy to see you again,
Ligaya.

211
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:32,200
But...

212
00:17:33,567 --> 00:17:34,900
maybe...

213
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:40,933
people like me...

214
00:17:44,567 --> 00:17:46,533
no longer have hope of getting
better.

215
00:17:48,833 --> 00:17:50,333
no longer have hope of changing.

216
00:17:54,967 --> 00:17:55,967
Maybe...

217
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:01,033
I shouldn't have shown up
to you.

218
00:18:03,767 --> 00:18:05,100
Maybe...

219
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:09,567
I'm better off alone.

220
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:53,867
No. The match is not over yet.

221
00:19:55,467 --> 00:20:01,033
Do you think Olive Caparas
will give up?

222
00:20:04,733 --> 00:20:09,467
I have tricks that Emma
hasn't seen yet.

223
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:20,633
Jade?

224
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:26,033
What happened to you?

225
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:27,300
Are you okay?

226
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:30,100
What did the doctor say?

227
00:20:30,233 --> 00:20:31,433
Is there any damage?

228
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:34,967
Quiet.

229
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,633
I'm talking to someone.

230
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:42,833
Where are you?

231
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:44,033
Talk to me.

232
00:20:54,767 --> 00:20:55,767
Give me one.

233
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,200
I need one more.

234
00:20:59,867 --> 00:21:01,767
Is this the drug you're taking?

235
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,900
This isn't Pryvaxil.

236
00:21:07,167 --> 00:21:08,067
What?

237
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,733
Jade, this is Z-X.

238
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:11,467
Zentrixia-X.

239
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:13,467
Hallucinogen.

240
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:14,533
What do you mean?

241
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,533
Look.

242
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:23,500
Z-X is one of the drugs I sold
before.

243
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:25,867
And I'm very familiar
with this one.

244
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,367
Look.

245
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:30,967
Pryvaxil is whiter
and has softer edges.

246
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,600
Jade, someone has tampered
with your medicine.

247
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:38,933
Jade, someone has tampered
with your medicine.

248
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:45,733
Flor needs a job, Auntie.

249
00:21:49,767 --> 00:21:50,967
It was Flor.

250
00:21:53,367 --> 00:21:55,800
She had been replacing
my medicines.

251
00:21:59,033 --> 00:22:00,433
Emma told her to do that.

252
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:04,167
So that's why your paranoia
got worse

253
00:22:04,300 --> 00:22:06,300
instead of calming you down.

254
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:08,333
That's why you've
been hallucinating.

255
00:22:10,967 --> 00:22:12,833
Damn you, Emma.

256
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:19,033
I won't let you win in your
games anymore.

257
00:22:21,333 --> 00:22:23,467
Do you want a bloody fight?

258
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:29,500
I will give you a bloodbath.

259
00:22:54,333 --> 00:22:57,000
Mookie, I've talked to my mom.

260
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:59,533
I made her confess what she told
you.

261
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:05,867
Zayn, I've thought
about it already.

262
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:09,467
And...

263
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:11,067
I'm done with this.

264
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:12,733
No!

265
00:23:12,867 --> 00:23:15,200
Why are you saying that?
We're not done yet.

266
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:22,133
Zayn, everything your mom said
was true.

267
00:23:23,233 --> 00:23:25,133
It's all true.

268
00:23:27,567 --> 00:23:30,967
She just made me realize
the reality.

269
00:23:32,300 --> 00:23:39,133
That I might also have
mental issues like Mommy Olive,

270
00:23:39,267 --> 00:23:41,433
Aunt Jade, and Mom.

271
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:44,533
And I might end up hurting you.

272
00:23:45,733 --> 00:23:49,567
So I have to let you go, Zayn.

273
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:51,900
I won't let you do that, Mookie.

274
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:53,233
I love my mom.

275
00:23:53,367 --> 00:23:55,367
But I can't let her dictate
my life.

276
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:57,233
What will happen, Zayn?

277
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:58,667
Are you going to fight with her?

278
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,767
No!

279
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:01,933
You're not your mom.
You're not your Aunt Jade.

280
00:24:02,067 --> 00:24:03,733
Mookie, you don't have
a mental issue.

281
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:07,267
Zayn, you won't win against your
mom.

282
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:11,067
You will just end up fighting.

283
00:24:12,233 --> 00:24:15,600
And I don't want your
relationship to get ruined.

284
00:24:15,733 --> 00:24:18,133
Zayn, I don't want you
to lose her.

285
00:24:20,267 --> 00:24:22,833
Because I know how it feels
to lose a mom.

286
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,233
It's painful.

287
00:24:27,433 --> 00:24:28,500
It's hard.

288
00:24:31,367 --> 00:24:36,033
That's why I want you
to choose her.

289
00:24:37,233 --> 00:24:39,900
I want you to choose your mom.

290
00:24:41,633 --> 00:24:44,200
I want you to choose your mom.

291
00:24:44,333 --> 00:24:46,733
Mookie, no.

292
00:24:46,967 --> 00:24:48,367
Let me fight for you.

293
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:49,933
Please.

294
00:24:50,067 --> 00:24:52,567
We can still be friends.

295
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:54,900
I don't want to be friends,
Mookie!

296
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:57,167
I don't want us
to be just friends.

297
00:24:57,300 --> 00:25:01,933
It's either you let me fight
for you or lose me completely,

298
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:03,467
even as a friend.

299
00:25:04,833 --> 00:25:06,667
I'll take care of my mom.

300
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,400
Don't you trust me?

301
00:25:08,533 --> 00:25:11,067
Zayn, I trust you.

302
00:25:12,133 --> 00:25:14,333
But do you know what
I'm not sure of?

303
00:25:16,233 --> 00:25:18,300
I'm not sure what will happen
to you

304
00:25:18,433 --> 00:25:20,267
after you lose your mom.

305
00:25:21,467 --> 00:25:23,267
Because look at me, Zayn.

306
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:26,733
You saw what happened to me,
right?

307
00:25:26,867 --> 00:25:28,433
You're unfair, Mooks.

308
00:25:29,900 --> 00:25:31,000
I'm here,

309
00:25:32,033 --> 00:25:34,067
willing to risk everything
for you.

310
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:38,100
But you can't do the
same thing for me.

311
00:25:38,267 --> 00:25:39,967
You don't love me enough.

312
00:25:40,100 --> 00:25:41,400
But fine.

313
00:25:41,533 --> 00:25:43,333
I'll do what you want.

314
00:25:43,467 --> 00:25:44,533
I'll choose Mom.

315
00:25:46,333 --> 00:25:48,800
But don't expect us
to still be friends.

316
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:15,567
I've finally found you,
Miss Ligaya.

317
00:26:23,133 --> 00:26:27,000
You're very much ready to
take your daughter back.

318
00:26:27,133 --> 00:26:31,833
I know that Artemis Pharmacy
is the baby of my sister, Olive.

319
00:26:31,967 --> 00:26:33,833
Now that she's gone,

320
00:26:33,967 --> 00:26:36,367
I want to reassure all of you

321
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:42,133
that I will continue the good
practices she had started.

322
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:46,933
Here's to a better,
brighter Artemis.
